## Gong Engage Flows visibility — permission set gap
**Problem:** A user reported the Engage Flows quick link wasn't visible on Contact 
records, despite it existing on admin views — initial ask read as a simple layout 
change ("add the link").

**Diagnosis:** Investigated via SOQL/Tooling API across profile, page layout 
assignment, Lightning Record Page assignment, and permission sets. Root cause: 
the user had zero Gong-related permission sets assigned. A dedicated permission 
set existed for this exact feature but had only been rolled out to a service 
account, not end users — the Lightning component was silently hiding itself 
without the right permission, rather than erroring.

**Resolution:** Assigned the appropriate permission set based on the user's role 
and existing access patterns of similar users.

**Takeaway:** Surfaced a gap between feature deployment and permission rollout — 
the underlying access was never extended to the team that needed it.
